1)SYSTEM PROMPT - the system prompt is set of instruction ,rules and role that is given to the AI model. EX- Act like game developer , you must give the data till the knowledge base etc
USER PROMPT - it is the question the user opted for. EX- what is the design of the game

2) a)LLM- it is an AI model which is trained on large amount of data which can understand , generate tasks
b)API-An API is that allows a client to communicate with a server by sending requests and receiving responses.
With GET requests, the client asks the server for data, with POST requests, the client sends data (payload) to the server.‚Äù
c)inference- it is process of running LLM models to generate output
d)workflow- it is the flow of work by connecting different nodes to execute the process,allowing data to transfer through one node to another ,without manual help.

4)role-based prompting is that we should assign a role in the prompt , where the LLM can understand it and acts like the role that we assigned to it. then the ouput will be better and we can set any guideline for the best format output
EX- act like a doctor, now read the below medical files and give me the diagnosis of the report.
guidelines - 1) I want in point wise information
             2)I want exact diagnosis in single line
             3)give me the medications for the dignoised disease

